GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 810
Short Title: Even-Year Municipal Elections/Catawba Co. (Local)
Sponsors: Senator Hollo (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
April 22, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE THAT REGULAR MUNICIPAL ELECTIONS FOR ALL
3 MUNICIPALITIES IN CATAWBA COUNTY BE HELD IN EVEN-NUMBERED
4 YEARS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6
7 TOWN OF BROOKFORD
8 SECTION 1.(a) Section 3 of the Charter of the Town of Brookford, being Chapter
9 230 of the Private Laws of 1907, as amended by Chapter 109 of the 1961 Session Laws and
10 Town Ordinance, reads as rewritten:
11 "Sec. 3. That the officers of the said corporation shall be a mayor, three commissioners and
12 such other officers and agents as may be appointed by the board of commissioners to enforce
13 their ordinances, keep their records, and otherwise aid in the conduct of the affairs of the town.
14 That until Tuesday after the first Monday in May, one thousand nine hundred and seven, T. J.
15 Leonard is appointed to the office of mayor of said town, and W. H. Shuford, J. W. Ballew and
16 C. E. Cole are appointed commissioners thereof; that the said mayor and commissioners shall
17 hold their offices until their successors are elected and qualified, as hereafter provided.The
18 officers of the Town of Brookford shall be a mayor and four aldermen. The term of office for
19 mayor shall be four years. The terms of office for the aldermen shall be four-year staggered
20 terms."
21 SECTION 1.(b) Section 4 of the Charter of the Town of Brookford, being Chapter
22 230 of the Private Laws of 1907, as amended by Chapter 109 of the 1961 Session Laws and
23 Town Ordinance, reads as rewritten:
24 "Sec. 4. That there shall be an election to the offices of mayor and commissioners of said
25 town on Tuesday after the first Monday in May, one thousand nine hundred and seven, and
26 biennially thereafter, under the same restrictions and regulations under which Shate and county
27 elections are held, and as provided by law for elections in cities and towns in North
28 Carolina.Regular municipal elections for officers in the Town of Brookford shall be held at the
29 time of the general election in each even-numbered year. The election shall be conducted on a
30 nonpartisan plurality basis and the results determined in accordance with G.S. 163-292. Except
31 as otherwise provided, the election shall be conducted in accordance with the uniform municipal
32 election laws in Chapter 163 of the General Statutes."
33 SECTION 1.(c) No municipal elections shall be conducted in the Town of Brookford
34 in 2027. The terms of office for the two aldermen in the Town of Brookford serving on the
35 effective date of this section whose terms are set to expire in 2027 shall be extended by one year.
36 The terms of office for the mayor and two aldermen in the Town of Brookford serving on the
*S810-v-1*

