29 CITY OF CLAREMONT
30 SECTION 3.(a) Section 3 of the Charter of the City of Claremont, being Chapter 11
31 of the Private Laws of 1893, as amended by Chapter 76 of the 1961 Session Laws, Chapter 97 of
32 the 1975 Session Laws, S.L. 2005-54, and Town Ordinance adopted on February 3, 1976, reads
33 as rewritten:
34 "Sec. 3. Elections; Terms of mayor and councilmen.council members.
35 (a) At the regular annual election of city officers in May, 1961, in the City of Claremont,
36 the qualified voters shall elect a mayor and five (5) councilmen.The governing body for the City
37 of Claremont shall consist of a mayor and five council members, elected to serve four-year
38 staggered terms. Regular municipal elections shall be held at the time of the general election in
39 each even-numbered year. Council members for the City of Claremont shall be elected on a
40 nonpartisan plurality basis and the results determined in accordance with G.S. 163-292. Except
41 as otherwise provided, the election shall be conducted in accordance with the uniform municipal
42 election laws in Chapter 163 of the General Statutes.
43 (b) The mayor to be elected in 2005 shall shall be elected to serve for a term of four years
44 or until a successor is duly elected and qualified. Thereafter, a mayor shall be elected every four
45 years in the odd-numbered years and the term of office shall be four years.
46 (c) Of the five (5) councilmen now holding office in the City of Claremont, Catawba
47 County, successors to the offices now held by Harold McRee Wilson, Eddy Gaither Harwell, and
48 William David Watts shall be elected at the November, 1975, election, and every four (4) years
49 thereafter, for the City of Claremont and shall serve for terms of four (4) years or until their
50 successors are elected and qualified. Successors to the offices now held by Timothy Allan
51 Lowrance and Gary Wayne Carpenter shall be elected at the regular November, 1977, election,
